channel.title: Silabsoft items are not on my sever
channel.description:
Hi I'm currently making a runescape private server (you may know) Called RUnescape RsPs..
Well i was testing loadsa stuff and i came across that my server does not have New jagex items.. such as godsword's, Dfs, Elegant...
How would i add these without having to use a client My server is 317 and i use the silabsoft client when playing my server
My base is
Legend The Hero's - Blank source

item.title: Silabsoft items are not on my sever
item.dc:creator: @bonzakid bonzakid
item.description:
@bonzakid wrote:

[quote=“MasterofPK, post:8, topic:273753”]This all comes down to your client.

If your using a client that you download you have to put the models in the models folder, and add the method into class8.java,

I’ve explained this before on other posts. You server files mean nothing unless you have the model (what is looks like etc.) added in and the method added.

Writing the words, "item = 9999 Dragon_full_helm A big Helmet. 1000 1000 1000 5 5 5 -7 -7 27 29 26 -3 28 0 0
In item.cfg won’t magically make a Dragon Full appear in your server.

Look for a tutorial on Adding items, or Adding Models.[/quote]
And that includes on the server aswell;…

Read full topic
